ter.com/BrianTMacdonald/status/1236353012744019969|title=We need to make @PeterMacKay the next leader of the Conservative Party of Canada!|first=Brian|last=Macdonald|date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Sohail Quadri]] (Alberta MLA for [[Edmonton-Mill Woods]], 2012-2015)\n*[[Peter Sandhu]] (Alberta MLA for [[Edmonton-Manning]], 2008-2015)\n*[[Ed Stelmach]] ([[Premier of Alberta]], 2006\u20132011) \n\n;'''Former municipal politicians:'''\n*Sandy McConkey ([[Springwater, Ontario|Springwater]] Township councillor for Ward 4, 2010-2018) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/McConkeySandy/status/1221123555619942406|title=Every Canadian needs to watch this!|first=Sandy|last=McConkey|date=25 January 2020}}</ref>\n;'''Other prominent individuals:'''\n*Dave Blackburn (MacKay's [[Outaouais]] chair, university professor at the [[Universit\u00e9 du Qu\u00e9bec en Outaouais]], 2019 candidate in [[Pontiac (electoral district)|Pontiac]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/BLACKBURNPONTIAC2019/posts/2698210086928737|title=I am very pleased to announce that I will be serving as the Outaouais Chair of Peter MacKay's campaign for the leadership of the Conservative Party of Canada.|publisher=Facebook|first=Dave|last=Blackburn|date=25 January 2020|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref>\n*Bryan Brulotte ([[Ottawa]] businessman; [[Conservative Party of Canada]] leadership contestant, 2020)<ref name=\"Brulottejan\"/>\n*[[George Canyon]] (country music singer and 2019 Candidate in [[Central Nova]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MarieAdsettCTV/status/1221086723821723648?s=20|title=George Canyon warming up the crowd.|last=Adsett|first=Marie|date=25 January 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Tom Flanagan (political scientist)|Tom Flanagan]] (former advisor to prime minister [[Stephen Harper]])<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/opinion/article-now-more-than-ever-peter-mackay-is-the-right-choice-for-conservative/|title=Now more than ever, Peter MacKay is the right choice for Conservative leader|date=21 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n;'''Organizations:''' \n* [[University of Guelph]] Campus Conservatives<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/guelphcons/posts/2810204765690076|title=Guelph Campus Conservatives|website=facebook.com}}</ref> \n;'''Media:'''\n}}\n\n===Erin O'Toole===\n[[File:Erin O'Toole.jpg|thumb|upright|Erin O'Toole]]\n;Background\n[[Erin O'Toole]], {{age|1973|1|22}}, is the MP for [[Durham (electoral district)|Durham]] (2012\u2013present), the Shadow Minister of Foreign Affairs (2017\u2013present), and the former Shadow Minister of Public Safety and Emergency Preparedness (2015\u20132016) and [[Minister of Veterans Affairs (Canada)|Minister of Veterans Affairs]] (2015). He placed third in the [[2017 Conservative Party of Canada leadership election|2017 Conservative leadership election]]. Prior to entering politics, O'Toole served as a [[Captain (Canadian army and air force)|captain]] in the [[Royal Canadian Air Force]] and was a lawyer after completing military service.<ref name=\"starpros\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/politics/federal/2019/12/12/rona-ambrose-peter-mackay-erin-otoole-cited-as-possible-contenders-to-replace-andrew-scheer-as-conservative-leader.html|title=Rona Ambrose, Peter MacKay, Erin O'Toole cited as possible contenders to replace Andrew Scheer as Conservative Leader|date=12 December 2019|work=Toronto Star|access-date=12 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n:'''Candidacy announced:''' 25 January 2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/davidakin/status/1221100162271121410|title=And @ErinOTooleMP makes it official|last=Akin  |first=David|date=25 January 2020|website=@davidakin|access-date=25 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6461702/erin-otoole-conservative-leadership-bid/|title=Erin O'Toole to announce formal bid for Conservative leadership|last=Jackson|first=Hannah|date=25 January 2020|website=Global News|access-date=25 January 2020}}</ref>\n:'''Date registered with Elections Can